@node INTRO "iNTRODUCTION"

  .------------.
  |iNTRODUCTION|
  `------------'

Hello, as some of you may know mAGNUM cHAT used to come bundled with mAGNUM pAGER,
however I did not want to develope the pager anymore, so developement of mAGNUM
pAGER has been taken over by Dr.X =), now I have more time to concentrate on this.

This version has mainly been written for a speed increase, compared to the last
version its lightning fast, and the sysop and user can type at the same time with no
character loss!, it also has a few little features described below, that'll do for
the introduction as I want to get this released tonight =)

 .--------.
 |fEATURES|
 `--------'


                - Split Screen Chat
                - Pick from 5 Chat Styles   - mAGNUM sTYLE
                                            - YaanChat Style
                                            - MaxsChat Style
                                            - gREMLINS mAXScHAT
                                            - Chat-Page

                - Change the chat style by key press!

                - Pick 3 types of writing
                  modes!                    - Normal
                                            - 3l!73 =) (elite)
                                            - tAggEd (capatalised vowels)
                                            - BuMpY capital every other letter

                - Uses 'Del' key and Ctrl-L to clear chat window!
                - Really cool screen clear effect!
                - Freeze and Un-Freeze users time
                - Ctrl-Q Quits, Nothing Else!
                - Quick logoff option
                - Move cursor around using cursor keys =)
                - Multi-Select Raw Download Function (uses reqtools requestor)
                - Raw Upload, to specified directory!
                - Faaaaaast!!


Sound good? Then go to the @{"System Requirements" Link syreq} section! to check
if it will run on your system or...

 @{"    " Link MAIN} rETURN tO tHE mAIN mENU...

@endnode

@node syreq "sYSTEM rEQUIREMENTS"

 .-------------------.
 |sYSTEM rEQUIREMENTS|
 `-------------------'

   MaxsBBS Professional (reccomended) or MaxsBBS v1.54

   Needs at least 60k of memory

   OS 2.04 or above (for reqtools)


   And thats it!, its not exactly power hungry!, could easily run on an
   A500+....

   Ok, If It will run on your miggy go strait to the installation section,
   by clicking below...

    @{"    " Link INSTL} iNSTALLATION...

   Or you can go back to the main page...

    @{"    " Link MAIN} rETURN tO mAIN mENU...


@endnode

@node INSTL "iNSTALLATION"

 .------------.
 |iNSTALLATION|
 `------------'

Installation is pretty simple =)

Unlha the archive to 'Ram:' using the following command

    Lha x mAG^cH_11.lha Ram:

Then run the installer program located in the 'Ram Disk', unsurprisingly
its called 'Install' =) Then just follow the on screen prompts and the
door will be copied to the 'Doors:' assignment!

Now, go to the MAXS menu you want to install the door on... And do the
following...


    Key     Func    Extra   Lo Acc  Hi Acc  Path/Filename/Extra...
    ~~~     ~~~~    ~~~~~   ~~~~~~  ~~~~~~  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
     ?       34       0       ??      ??    DOORS:mAGNUMcHAT/mAGNUMcHAT


Replace the ? with the values or keys you want..

You would usually have the doors Lo Acc at sysops level so the remote
user cannot access it, unless you run a BBS for insane people who like
chatting to themselves =)


 .-------------.
 |cONFIGURATION|
 `-------------'

Right, now you have installed mAGNUM cHAT you need to configure it!, this
is easy!


Ok, load the 'DOORS:mAGNUMcHAT/mAGNUMcHAT.cfg' into your ASCII editor
and edit it to what you want..


Line 1:  Directory to place Raw Uploads, Include trailing : or /
Line 2:  Chat Style, 0 = Magnum, 1=YaanChat, 2=MaxsChat 3=gREMLINS mAXcHAT 4=ChatPage
Line 3:  Screen Clearing Mode, 0=Normal, 1=Scroller (cool!)
Line 4:  End Of Config

You MUST include a trailing : or / on line 1 otherwise the Raw Upload
feature will not put the file in the correct path..

The chat style you select is the default when you first run mAGNUM cHAT, these can be
scrolled through using 'Ctrl-C'...

Try out the new screen clearing effect!, I hope you'll like it!

Example config:

Work:Sysops/
2
1
#

And your done!, told you it was easy!

Now go to the section on how to use this great door, by clicking below...

 @{"    " Link USAGE} uSING mAGNUM cHAT...

Or you can go back to the main menu by clicking below this line :)

 @{"    " Link MAIN} rETURN tO mAIN mENU...


@endnode

@node USAGE "uSING tHE dOORS!"

 .-------.
 | USAGE |
 `-------'

Now you get to try mAGNUM cHAT out!

This chat door has many features that are easily accesible by key presses :)

Ok, here is a list and a short description of the chatters functions!

    DEL      -  Clear Your Chat Window
    Ctrl-L   -  Clear Your Chat Window
    Ctrl-N   -  Clear Both Chat Windows

    Ctrl-T   -  Time-Freeze  (SYSOP)
    Ctrl-U   -  Un-Freeze Time  (SYSOP)

    Ctrl-A   -  Raw Download (SYSOP)
    Ctrl-R   -  Raw Upload (SYSOP)

    Ctrl-Z   -  Quick LogOff (SYSOP)
    Ctrl-W   -  Writing Mode Select  (SYSOP)
    Ctrl-C   -  Cycles through chat styles :) (SYSOP)

    Ctrl-Q   -  Quit Chatter

Cursor Keys  -  Move cursor around chat window (SYSOP)

Obviously, options marked (SYSOP) can only be operated
by the SysOp..

  .----------------------.
  |dECENT dESCRIPTIONS :)|
  `----------------------'

 --Screen Clearing--

mAGNUM cHAT uses the 'DEL' or 'Ctrl-L' keys to clear your window, this
makes it quick and easy to clear your window...

Ctrl-N Will Clear both the chat windows, good for clearing the users
window if there writing some thing you don't like or don't wont other
peepz in the room seeing =)

 --Time Freezing--

This option stops the user time decreasing, if you've been chatting
with a user for ages and they only have a few minutes left when you
finished chatting, there gonna get PO'ed, so you can stall the users
time using 'Ctrl-T' and resume the time count down using 'Ctrl-U',
when you quit the chat door time freezing will be turned off so dont
worry about turning it off before you quit...

 --Raw Downloads--

Isn't it really annoying when some one ask for a file and you've got
to quit the chat door, go past the security check etc. to use the raw
download feature? Wouldn't it be great to hit 'Ctrl-A' and a instant
multiselect requestor would pop up?, well thats what this does! And
you can select as many files as you want!

 --Raw Uploads--

Just Hit Ctrl-R and the Z-Modem recieve window will pop up,
Uploads will be placed in the directory you specified in the
configuration file!.

 --Writing Modes--

There are 4 different writing styles available, If any of you have
used YaanChat you'll know the other one (I didn't think it was worth
implementing, but if you want it let me know, I'll put it in the next
version), anyway heres the writing modes:

    Normal  -  Normal Writing

    Elite   -  Ыl!7Ы mиDЫ =) The Stuff you cant read (usually)

    Tagged  - cApAtAlIsEd vOwEls

    BuMpY   - eVeRy OtHeR lEtTeR iS cApAtAlIsEd

 --Quitting--


Ctrl-Q quits the chatter, Nothing else, Not the ESC key like in
MaxsChat (which caused problems)...

If the user wants to leave or your getting p*ssed off with them
you can use Ctrl-Z to do a quick logoff :) mAGNUM cHAT useses
the standard logoff command, so the BBS will reset mail pointers etc.

 --Cursor Keys--

The 4 arrowed cursor keys (the ones to the left of the numerical
key pad), are used to move the cursor around :), this is good
for doing ASCII drawing in the chat window (hmm, that would be
usefull for Techn!x if he ever comes back)...

Try           writing           in
   doing             like         the
        some             this        chatter!


Thats all the features! (So far) - Want more? Ask me!

 @{"    " Link MAIN} rETURN tO mAIN mENU...

